    <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
 	<!--translation encoded as per EG §9.2 -->
	<p>Om. Let there be no obstacle! As follows is the decree of Rahyang Niskala Wastu Kancana, that came down to Rahyang Ningrat Kancana and also to His Highness now at Pakuan Pajajaran.</p> 
	<p>Do not omit to take care of the inhabitants of Jayagiri and the inhabitants of Sundasembawa.</p> 
	<p>If there is someone providing them livelihood, don’t be eager to overcrowd/overburden him/them with the <foreign xml:lang="x-oldsun-Latn">dasa</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="x-oldsun-Latn">calagara</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="x-oldsun-Latn">kapas timbang</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="x-oldsun-Latn">pare dongdang</foreign>.</p> 
	<p>Also addressed to all the <supplied reason="subaudible">people at the</supplied> mouth of the river: don’t be eager to ask them toll. Because those who are loved, as it were, <supplied reason="subaudible">themselves</supplied> love the world, who firmly put into practice the divine ordinances.</p> 
         </div>
